 ### Status
 All 194 tests passing (169 existing + 25 new). TypeScript compiles cleanly.
+
+---
+
+## Agent 9 — Multi-Channel User Notification Preferences (completed)
+
+### What was done
+Refactored user preferences from email-only to per-channel settings (email, SMS, webhook), addressing the gap flagged by Agent 8.
+
+1. **Updated `src/models/user-preferences.ts`**:
+   - Added `SmsPreferences` interface (enabled, subscribedCategories)
+   - Added `WebhookPreferences` interface (enabled, subscribedCategories, optional url)
+   - Extended `UserPreferences` with `sms` and `webhook` fields alongside existing `email`
+   - Extended `CreatePreferencesInput` and `UpdatePreferencesInput` with optional `sms` and `webhook` fields
+   - Added `DEFAULT_SMS_PREFERENCES` and `DEFAULT_WEBHOOK_PREFERENCES` constants
+   - Updated module docstring to document the decision change
+
+2. **Updated `src/repositories/preferences.repository.ts`**:
+   - `toDomain()` now deserializes `sms` and `webhook` fields, falling back to defaults for backward compatibility with records created before this change
+   - `toRecord()` now serializes `sms` and `webhook` fields
+
+3. **Updated `src/services/preferences.service.ts`**:
+   - `createPreferences()` merges SMS and webhook defaults with provided input
+   - `updatePreferences()` handles partial updates for all three channels
+   - `shouldSendNotification()` now checks per-channel preferences for `'sms'` and `'webhook'` channels (enabled toggle + subscribedCategories), instead of defaulting to `true`
+
+4. **Updated `src/index.ts`** — exports for `SmsPreferences`, `WebhookPreferences`, `DEFAULT_SMS_PREFERENCES`, `DEFAULT_WEBHOOK_PREFERENCES`
+
+5. **Created 28 tests** in `tests/services/preferences.service.test.ts`:
+   - Create preferences: defaults for all channels, per-channel overrides, custom subscribedCategories, duplicate prevention
+   - Update preferences: single channel update, multi-channel update, subscribedCategories update, error handling
+   - getOrCreatePreferences: existing + new user paths
+   - shouldSendNotification: email (enabled, frequency, categories), SMS (enabled, categories), webhook (enabled, categories), cross-channel independence, unknown channel fallback
+   - Delete preferences: success + error
+
+### Decision change documented
+**The email-only assumption from Session 3 is explicitly invalidated.** The preferences model now supports per-channel settings. This was driven by the addition of SMS (Session 8) and webhook (Session 6) adapters — without multi-channel preferences, users could not opt out of SMS/webhook notifications.
+
+### Backward compatibility
+- Existing code that only sets `email` preferences continues to work — SMS and webhook get sensible defaults
+- The repository `toDomain()` handles records without `sms`/`webhook` fields by applying defaults
+- `shouldSendNotification()` still returns `true` for unknown channels (e.g., `in_app`)
+- All existing tests pass without modification
+
+### Status
+All 222 tests passing (194 existing + 28 new). TypeScript compiles cleanly.
